Q1 - The test is useless when we have not a clear vision to the requirement or the specifications are not defined ,
 than we can not be able to test a product within knowing the definition of done .

Q2 - Testing can show that defects are present, but cannot prove that there are no defects. Testing reduces
    the probability of undiscovered defects remaining in the software .

Q3 - Acceptance testing,typically focuses on the behavior and capabilities of a whole system or product , than API unit
 testing focuses on components focuses on components that are separately testable : for example in the bank system
 tester can test the behaviour of transaction as user vision and simulate an action of debiting an account (UI Acceptance testing)
and the other side he can test the transaction has debited by a Api unit test ib the code .

Q4-The main benefit of ISTQB certification is to make tester able to have many basics knowledge in Software Quality and
be able to integrate the word QA community by following the unit ISTQI testing process, but the istqb is not the unique
source of the tester and we have many parts missing as advanced performance tests certification .

