 Q6- Regression testing: is defined as a type of software testing to confirm that a recent program or code change
 has not adversely affected existing features.Regression Testing is nothing but a full or partial or local selection
 of already executed test cases which are re-executed to ensure existing functionalities work fine. regression test is
 a good always a good candidate for automation.

