 Q8 - Gherkin is a syntax for BDD and Cucumber is a tool that supports Behaviour-Driven Development(BDD).
Than the BDD (Behaviour-Driven Development)  is an approach that consists on defining the behavior of a feature through
 examples in plain text. These examples are defined before the development starts and are used as acceptance criteria.
  They are part of the definition of done

